{"name": "adafruit-circuitpython-requests", "metadata": {"name": "adafruit-circuitpython-requests", "version": "4.1.8", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Software Development :: Embedded Systems", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: System :: Hardware"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["Adafruit-Blinka", "Adafruit-Circuitpython-ConnectionManager"], "summary": "A requests-like library for web interfacing", "upload_time": 1728340492}, "documentation": ["# Introduction\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/adafruit-circuitpython-requests/badge/?version=latest\n:alt: Documentation Status\n:target: https://docs.circuitpython.org/projects/requests/en/latest/\n```\n\n```{image} https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Bundle/main/badges/adafruit_discord.svg\n:alt: Discord\n:target: https://adafru.it/discord\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Requests/workflows/Build%20CI/badge.svg\n:alt: Build Status\n:target: https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Requests/actions/\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/astral-sh/ruff/main/assets/badge/v2.json\n:alt: 'Code Style: Ruff'\n:target: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff\n```\n\nA requests-like library for HTTP commands.\n\n# Dependencies\n\nThis driver depends on:\n\n- [Adafruit CircuitPython](https://github.com/adafruit/circuitpython)\n- [Adafruit CircuitPython ConnectionManager](https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_ConnectionManager/)\n\nPlease ensure all dependencies are available on the CircuitPython filesystem.\nThis is easily achieved by downloading\n[the Adafruit library and driver bundle](https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Bundle).\n\n# Installing from PyPI\n\nOn supported GNU/Linux systems like the Raspberry Pi, you can install the driver locally [from\nPyPI](https://pypi.org/project/adafruit-circuitpython-requests/). To install for current user:\n\n```shell\npip3 install adafruit-circuitpython-requests\n```\n\nTo install system-wide (this may be required in some cases):\n\n```shell\nsudo pip3 install adafruit-circuitpython-requests\n```\n\nTo install in a virtual environment in your current project:\n\n```shell\nmkdir project-name && cd project-name\npython3 -m venv .venv\nsource .venv/bin/activate\npip3 install adafruit-circuitpython-requests\n```\n\n# Usage Example\n\nUsage examples are within the `examples` subfolder of this library.\n\n# Documentation\n\nAPI documentation for this library can be found on [Read the Docs](https://docs.circuitpython.org/projects/requests/en/latest/).\n\nFor information on building library documentation, please check out [this guide](https://learn.adafruit.com/creating-and-sharing-a-circuitpython-library/sharing-our-docs-on-readthedocs#sphinx-5-1).\n\n# Contributing\n\nContributions are welcome! Please read our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Requests/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\nbefore contributing to help this project stay welcoming.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "adafruit_requests", "documentation": ["`adafruit_requests`\n================================================================================\n\nA requests-like library for web interfacing\n\n\n* Author(s): ladyada, Paul Sokolovsky, Scott Shawcroft\n\nImplementation Notes\n--------------------\n\nAdapted from https://github.com/micropython/micropython-lib/tree/master/urequests\n\nmicropython-lib consists of multiple modules from different sources and\nauthors. Each module comes under its own licensing terms. Short name of\na license can be found in a file within a module directory (usually\nmetadata.txt or setup.py). Complete text of each license used is provided\nat https://github.com/micropython/micropython-lib/blob/master/LICENSE\n\nauthor='Paul Sokolovsky'\nlicense='MIT'\n\n**Software and Dependencies:**\n\n* Adafruit CircuitPython firmware for the supported boards:\n  https://github.com/adafruit/circuitpython/releases\n\n* Adafruit's Connection Manager library:\n  https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_ConnectionManager", "SPDX-FileCopyrightText: 2019 ladyada for Adafruit Industries", "SPDX-FileCopyrightText: 2020 Scott Shawcroft for Adafruit Industries", "SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "adafruit_requests.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adafruit_requests.__repo__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adafruit_requests.SEEK_END", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "adafruit_requests._RawResponse", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "adafruit_requests._RawResponse.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "response", "type": {"name": "Response", "xref": {"fqname": "Response", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "adafruit_requests._RawResponse.read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "size", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Read as much as available or up to size and return it in a byte string.\n\nDo NOT use this unless you really need to. Reusing memory with `readinto` is much better."]}, {"name": "adafruit_requests._RawResponse.readinto", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "buf", "type": {"name": "bytearray", "xref": {"fqname": "funct